Key Takeaways:

API Security is beyond software or common library vulnerabilities, which includes flaws in business logic, authentication, data validation, improper asset management etc.,
Ensure robust authentication and authorization mechanisms.
Implement strong input validation to prevent injection attacks.
Regularly monitor and log API activity.
Keep your API inventory updated and well-managed.
